This paper is about designing prediction markets, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of understanding the participants' signal structure, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves constructing informative markets, which is related to economics and econometrics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses formal frameworks and considers the design of markets, which are topics in computer science (cs.DS).
